{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775826394586,"sessionID":"ses_288822a77ffew8zG4LGC9Q7q95","part":{"id":"prt_d778059ad001mBB3huQ6AolbI4","messageID":"msg_d77804754001E6a8W0Oa2n4XXp","sessionID":"ses_288822a77ffew8zG4LGC9Q7q95","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_d4e321d4fa9848b3944081c9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-009/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-009/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-009: Router HTTP 反向代理核心 — 设计说明\n2: \n3: ## 1. 架构\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 定位\n6: \n7: <!-- TODO: 填写架构定位 -->\n8: \n9: ### 1.2 包结构\n10: \n11: <!-- TODO: 填写包结构 -->\n12: \n13: ### 1.3 依赖关系\n14: \n15: <!-- TODO: 填写依赖关系 -->\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 2. 数据结构\n20: \n21: <!-- TODO: 填写数据结构设计 -->\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## 3. API 契约\n26: \n27: <!-- TODO: 填写 API 契约 -->\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## 4. 错误处理\n32: \n33: <!-- TODO: 填写错误处理策略 -->\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## 5. 测试策略\n38: \n39: <!-- TODO: 填写测试策略 -->\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: ## 6. 实现步骤\n44: \n45: <!-- TODO: 填写实现步骤 -->\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ## 7. 后续变更\n50: \n51: <!-- TODO: 填写后续变更 -->\n\n(End of file - total 51 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-009: Router HTTP 反向代理核心 — 设计说明\n\n## 1. 架构\n\n### 1.1 定位\n\n<!-- TODO: 填写架构定位 -->\n\n### 1.2 包结构\n\n<!-- TODO: 填写包结构 -->\n\n### 1.3 依赖关系\n\n<!-- TODO: 填写依赖关系 -->\n\n---\n\n## 2. 数据结构\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-009/design.md","time":{"start":1775826394580,"end":1775826394585}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775826395769,"sessionID":"ses_288822a77ffew8zG4LGC9Q7q95","part":{"id":"prt_d77805e7f001ShctzET8GmeaYW","messageID":"msg_d77804754001E6a8W0Oa2n4XXp","sessionID":"ses_288822a77ffew8zG4LGC9Q7q95","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_0e7a4e84588740b9a5f4330c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-003: CRD 共享类型与常量\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: Extract shared types (`TargetPort`, `ProtocolType`) and constants from `codeinterpreter_types.go` into dedicated files, establishing a clear ownership model for the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package.\n6: \n7: **Module:** `pkg/apis`\n8: **Language:** Go\n9: **Size:** S\n10: \n11: ## Problem Statement\n12: \n13: The current codebase has several organizational issues:\n14: \n15: 1. **`TargetPort`** is defined in `codeinterpreter_types.go` but consumed by both `AgentRuntimeSpec.Ports` and `CodeInterpreterSpec.Ports`. This creates an implicit cross-CRD dependency and makes it unclear where new shared types should go.\n16: \n17: 2. **`ProtocolType`** and its constants (`ProtocolTypeHTTP`, `ProtocolTypeHTTPS`) live in `codeinterpreter_types.go` despite being semantically generic — any future CRD that exposes network ports would need to reference them.\n18: \n19: 3. **No dedicated file for shared types.** As the API surface grows (e.g., future CRDs like `SessionManager`, `Gateway`), there is no canonical location for types shared across CRDs.\n20: \n21: 4. **Kind constants and `SchemeGroupVersion`** are split between `register.go` and `groupversion_info.go`. While functional, the separation is inconsistent with the kubebuilder convention of a single `groupversion_info.go`.\n22: \n23: ## Goals\n24: \n25: - Provide a canonical home for types and constants shared across CRDs within the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n26: - Maintain 100% backward compatibility — no import path changes, no API-breaking renames.\n27: - Keep CRD-specific types (`AuthModeType`, `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`, `SandboxTemplate`) in their respective type files.\n28: - Ensure `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` continues to regenerate correctly.\n29: \n30: ## Non-Goals\n31: \n32: - Multi-version API support (v1beta1, v2, etc.)\n33: - CRD validation webhook scaffolding\n34: - Conversion webhook setup\n35: \n36: ## Design\n37: \n38: ### File Structure\n39: \n40: ```\n41: pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/\n42: ├── doc.go                        # unchanged\n43: ├── groupversion_info.go          # merge: absorb SchemeGroupVersion + Resource() from register.go\n44: ├── types.go                      # NEW: shared types (TargetPort, ProtocolType)\n45: ├── constants.go                  # NEW: shared constants (ProtocolTypeHTTP, ProtocolTypeHTTPS)\n46: ├── agent_type.go                 # remove TargetPort/ProtocolType references → import from types.go (same package, no import change)\n47: ├── codeinterpreter_types.go      # remove TargetPort/ProtocolType/AuthModeType → keep only AuthModeType + CRD types\n48: ├── register.go                   # REMOVE: contents merged into groupversion_info.go\n49: ├── zz_generated.deepcopy.go      # regenerated\n50: └── *_test.go                     # updated to match new file layout\n51: ```\n52: \n53: ### New File: `types.go`\n54: \n55: Contains types shared across multiple CRDs within the same API version.\n56: \n57: ```go\n58: package v1alpha1\n59: \n60: // ProtocolType defines the network protocol for port exposure.\n61: type ProtocolType string\n62: \n63: const (\n64: \tProtocolTypeHTTP  ProtocolType = \"HTTP\"\n65: \tProtocolTypeHTTPS ProtocolType = \"HTTPS\"\n66: )\n67: \n68: // TargetPort describes a network port exposed by a sandbox runtime.\n69: type TargetPort struct {\n70: \tPathPrefix string       `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n71: \tName       string       `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n72: \tPort       uint32       `json:\"port\"`\n73: \tProtocol   ProtocolType `json:\"protocol\"`\n74: }\n75: ```\n76: \n77: **Rationale:** `ProtocolType` and its constants are co-located because the constants have no meaning without the type. `TargetPort` is placed in the same file because it is the primary consumer of `ProtocolType` and is itself shared.\n78: \n79: ### New File: `constants.go`\n80: \n81: Reserved for future shared constants that are not tied to a specific type (e.g., well-known annotation keys, label selectors, default values). Initially empty or minimal:\n82: \n83: ```go\n84: package v1alpha1\n85: \n86: // Well-known annotation keys used across AgentCube CRDs.\n87: const (\n88: \tAnnotationKeyRuntime = \"agentcube.io/runtime\"\n89: \tAnnotationKeyVersion = \"agentcube.io/version\"\n90: )\n91: ```\n92: \n93: **Rationale:** These annotation strings are currently duplicated inline in test files. Centralizing them prevents drift and enables `kubectl get` label selectors to reference a single source of truth.\n94: \n95: ### Modified: `groupversion_info.go`\n96: \n97: Absorbs the contents of `register.go` to follow the kubebuilder convention of a single group-version info file:\n98: \n99: ```go\n100: package v1alpha1\n101: \n102: import (\n103: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema\"\n104: \t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/scheme\"\n105: )\n106: \n107: var (\n108: \tGroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}\n109: \n110: \t// SchemeGroupVersion is an alias to GroupVersion for backward compatibility\n111: \t// with client-go generated code that references this name.\n112: \tSchemeGroupVersion = GroupVersion\n113: \n114: \tSchemeBuilder = &scheme.Builder{GroupVersion: GroupVersion}\n115: \n116: \tAddToScheme = SchemeBuilder.AddToScheme\n117: )\n118: \n119: // Resource returns the GroupVersionResource for the given resource name.\n120: func Resource(resource string) schema.GroupVersionResource {\n121: \treturn GroupVersion.WithResource(resource)\n122: }\n123: \n124: // Kind constants for both CRDs.\n125: var (\n126: \tCodeInterpreterKind             = \"CodeInterpreter\"\n127: \tCodeInterpreterGroupKind        = GroupVersion.WithKind(\"CodeInterpreter\")\n128: \tCodeInterpreterListKind         = \"CodeInterpreterList\"\n129: \tCodeInterpreterGroupVersionKind = GroupVersion.WithKind(\"CodeInterpreter\")\n130: \n131: \tAgentRuntimeKind             = \"AgentRuntime\"\n132: \tAgentRuntimeListKind         = \"AgentRuntimeList\"\n133: \tAgentRuntimeGroupVersionKind = GroupVersion.WithKind(\"AgentRuntime\")\n134: )\n135: ```\n136: \n137: ### Modified: `codeinterpreter_types.go`\n138: \n139: Remove `ProtocolType`, its constants, and `TargetPort`. Keep `AuthModeType` (CRD-specific) and the CodeInterpreter CRD types:\n140: \n141: ```go\n142: package v1alpha1\n143: \n144: import (\n145: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n146: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n147: )\n148: \n149: // AuthModeType defines the authentication mode for CodeInterpreter.\n150: type AuthModeType string\n151: \n152: const (\n153: \tAuthModePicoD AuthModeType = \"picod\"\n154: \tAuthModeNone  AuthModeType = \"none\"\n155: )\n156: \n157: // +genclient\n158: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n159: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n160: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n161: // +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced\n162: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n163: type CodeInterpreter struct { ... }\n164: \n165: // ... (CodeInterpreterSpec, CodeInterpreterStatus, CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate, CodeInterpreterList unchanged)\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ### Modified: `agent_type.go`\n169: \n170: No structural changes — `TargetPort` and `ProtocolType` remain accessible because they are in the same package. The file continues to compile without modification.\n171: \n172: ### Deleted: `register.go`\n173: \n174: All contents merged into `groupversion_info.go`. The `Resource()` helper and Kind constants are now co-located with `GroupVersion` and `SchemeBuilder`.\n175: \n176: ## Backward Compatibility\n177: \n178: | Concern | Resolution |\n179: |---------|-----------|\n180: | Import paths | No change — all types remain in `package v1alpha1` |\n181: | Type names | No renames — `TargetPort`, `ProtocolType`, `ProtocolTypeHTTP`, etc. keep their identifiers |\n182: | JSON serialization | Unchanged — struct tags are preserved |\n183: | `SchemeGroupVersion` alias | Preserved for client-go generated code |\n184: | `Resource()` helper | Preserved with identical signature |\n185: | Kind constants | Preserved with identical names and values |\n186: | DeepCopy methods | Regenerated by `make gen-client`; `TargetPort.DeepCopyInto` is a no-op copy (all fields are value types) |\n187: \n188: ## Testing Strategy\n189: \n190: ### Unit Tests\n191: \n192: | Test File | Coverage |\n193: |-----------|----------|\n194: | `types_test.go` | `ProtocolType` constant values, `TargetPort` zero-value defaults, `TargetPort` DeepCopy isolation |\n195: | `constants_test.go` | Well-known annotation key values |\n196: | `groupversion_info_test.go` (updated) | All Kind constants, `SchemeGroupVersion` alias, `Resource()` helper, scheme registration for both CRDs |\n197: | `agent_type_test.go` (unchanged) | Existing tests continue to pass — `TargetPort` and `ProtocolType` are still accessible from the same package |\n198: | `codeinterpreter_types_test.go` (unchanged) | Existing tests continue to pass — `AuthModeType` remains in the same file |\n199: \n200: ### Test Cases for `types_test.go`\n201: \n202: ```\n203: TestProtocolTypeConstants\n204:   - ProtocolTypeHTTP == \"HTTP\"\n205:   - ProtocolTypeHTTPS == \"HTTPS\"\n206:   - ProtocolTypeHTTP != ProtocolTypeHTTPS\n207: \n208: TestTargetPortDefaults\n209:   - Zero-value TargetPort: Port==0, empty Name/PathPrefix, empty Protocol\n210: \n211: TestTargetPortWithAllFields\n212:   - All fields set, verify JSON tags\n213: \n214: TestTargetPortDeepCopy\n215:   - DeepCopy produces independent copy\n216:   - Modifying copy does not affect original\n217: ```\n218: \n219: ### Test Cases for `constants_test.go`\n220: \n221: ```\n222: TestWellKnownAnnotationKeys\n223:   - AnnotationKeyRuntime == \"agentcube.io/runtime\"\n224:   - AnnotationKeyVersion == \"agentcube.io/version\"\n225: ```\n226: \n227: ### Regression Tests\n228: \n229: Run the full existing test suite to verify no breakage:\n230: \n231: ```bash\n232: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/... -v\n233: ```\n234: \n235: All existing tests must pass without modification (same-package visibility ensures `TargetPort` and `ProtocolType` remain accessible).\n236: \n237: ## Code Generation\n238: \n239: After file restructuring, regenerate:\n240: \n241: ```bash\n242: make gen-client\n243: ```\n244: \n245: This runs `hack/update-codegen.sh` which invokes `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 with `--with-watch`. Expected output:\n246: \n247: - `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` — regenerated with `TargetPort` DeepCopy methods (no functional change, as `TargetPort` contains only value types)\n248: - `client-go/` — no changes (generated code references types by package, not by file)\n249: \n250: ## Migration Steps\n251: \n252: 1. Create `types.go` with `ProtocolType`, its constants, and `TargetPort`\n253: 2. Create `constants.go` with well-known annotation keys\n254: 3. Merge `register.go` contents into `groupversion_info.go`\n255: 4. Delete `register.go`\n256: 5. Remove `ProtocolType`, its constants, and `TargetPort` from `codeinterpreter_types.go`\n257: 6. Create `types_test.go` and `constants_test.go`\n258: 7. Update `register_test.go` → rename to `groupversion_info_test.go` (or merge)\n259: 8. Run `make gen-client` to regenerate DeepCopy\n260: 9. Run `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/... -v` to verify\n261: \n262: ## Risks and Mitigations\n263: \n264: | Risk | Mitigation |\n265: |------|-----------|\n266: | `make gen-client` fails due to file reorganization | The code generator scans the package, not individual files. As long as `doc.go` markers and type definitions are intact, regeneration succeeds. |\n267: | External consumers import specific files | Go imports are at the package level, not file level. No external breakage possible. |\n268: | Merge conflicts during active development | This is a small, self-contained refactoring (S size). Should be merged during a low-activity window. |\n\n(End of file - total 268 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-003: CRD 共享类型与常量\n\n## Overview\n\nExtract shared types (`TargetPort`, `ProtocolType`) and constants from `codeinterpreter_types.go` into dedicated files, establishing a clear ownership model for the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package.\n\n**Module:** `pkg/apis`\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** S\n\n## Problem Statement\n\nThe current codebase has several organizational issues:\n\n1. **`TargetPort`** is defined in `codeinterpreter_types.go` but consumed by both `AgentRuntimeSpec.Ports` and `CodeInterpreterSpec.Ports`. This creates an implicit cross-CRD dependency and makes it unclear where new shared types should go.\n\n2. **`ProtocolType`** and its constants (`ProtocolTypeHTTP`, `ProtocolTypeHTTPS`) live in `codeinterpreter_types.go` despite being semantically generic — any future CRD that exposes network ports would need to reference them.\n\n3. **No dedicated file for shared types.** As the API surface grows (e.g., future CRDs like `SessionManager`, `Gateway`), there is no canonical location for types shared across CRDs.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775826395762,"end":1775826395767}}}}
